{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["Cardboard"], "type": "title", "extent": [69, 83], "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "extent": [83, 142], "text": ["Simulates a rough, anti-aliased cardboard surface."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [142, 208], "text": ["This operator simulates a rough, anti-aliased cardboard surface."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [208, 468], "text": ["If you are looking for a corrugated look, you can either use Furrows in\na separate displacement shader, or pipe the ", {"text": ["dispN"], "type": "code"}, " output of the\n", {"text": ["Furrows"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/furrows", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/furrows"}, " operator into the Normal (", {"text": ["N"], "type": "code"}, ") input of this operator as a bump map. We recommend the former."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [468, 883], "text": ["Other materials, such as ragged paper and rough walls can also be\nsimulated with this operator by changing the Surface Color (", {"text": ["scolor"], "type": "code"}, ")\ninput and possibly other parameters. Since all this operator does is a\nnoisy displacement followed by a call to the lighting model, it truly is\nmuch more generic than its name suggests. For example, it was used to\nsimulate grout in the ", {"text": ["Stone Wall"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/stonewall", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/stonewall"}, " operator."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [883, 1404], "text": ["If the Position (", {"text": ["P"], "type": "code"}, ") input and the Normal (", {"text": ["N"], "type": "code"}, ") input are not connected,\nthe global variables by the same names will be used instead. Typically\nyou will use ", {"text": ["Rest Position"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/restpos", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/restpos"}, " or ", {"text": ["UV Space Change"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/uvspacechg", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/uvspacechg"}, " as inputs for ", {"text": ["P"], "type": "code"}, ", and\nwill not touch ", {"text": ["N"], "type": "code"}, " unless you want to apply additional displacement to\nthe surface using an operator such as ", {"text": ["Furrows"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/furrows", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/furrows"}, ". If you need to access the\nglobal variables directly, they are available from the ", {"text": ["Global Variables"], "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/global", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/global"}, "\noperator."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1413, 1439], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/eggshell", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/eggshell"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1439, 1464], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/furrows", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/furrows"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1464, 1488], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/global", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/global"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1488, 1515], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/stonewall", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/stonewall"}]}, {"indent": 4, "blevel": 6, "type": "bullet", "extent": [1515, 1538], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/vop/wood", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/vop/wood"}]}], "container": true, "type": "bullet_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Related", "role": "section", "extent": [1404, 1413], "container": true, "type": "related_section", "id": "related"}], "summary": ["Simulates a rough, anti-aliased cardboard surface."], "type": "root", "attrs": {"version": null, "namespace": null, "internal": "cardboard", "context": "vop", "type": "node", "icon": "VOP/cardboard"}, "title": ["Cardboard"]}